OL,3,CMan jailed for three years for killing
OL,4,Cfriend in arson
OL,6,FMagee had originally been charged with
OL,7,Fmurder, but that was withdrawn when he
OL,8,Flater pleaded guilty to manslaughter
OL,9,Fand arson with intent to endanger
OL,10,Flife.JCrown court judge Madam Justice
OL,11,FMcBride told the court that on the
OL,12,Fevening of Mr Thompson's death, a
OL,13,Fneighbour had noticed smoke coming
OL,14,Ffrom his small terraced bungalow.JFire
OL,15,Fservice officers found Mr Thompson
OL,16,Funconscious on the floor in a bedroom.
OL,17,FHe was taken outside but died at the
OL,18,Fscene.JMagee was found near the back
OL,19,Fdoor and was taken to hospital to be
OL,20,Ftreated for smoke inhalation.JThe
OL,21,Fjudge said analysis had shown there
OL,22,Fhad been separate fires in the front
OL,23,Fbedroom, back bedroom and living room
OL,24,Fand accidental cause was ruled out.
OL,25,FDuring a police interview Magee had
OL,26,Foriginally denied lighting the fires.
